	<Title>
		Heart rate: What&apos;s normal?
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		A normal resting heart rate for adults ranges from 60 to 100 beats a minute. A heart rate above or below that may signal a problem.
	</Abstract>
	<Question>
		What&apos;s a normal resting heart rate?
	</Question>
